SIMPLE: obliquity
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Obliquity
<hw>Ob*liq"ui*ty</hw>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Obliquities</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[L.
<ets>obliquitas</ets>: cf. F. <ets>obliquit⟦eacute⟧</ets>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>The condition of being oblique; deviation from a right
line; deviation from parallelism or perpendicularity; the amount of such
deviation; divergence; <as>as, the <ex>obliquity</ex> of the ecliptic to
the equator</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Deviation from ordinary rules; irregularity;
deviation from moral rectitude.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>To disobey [God] . . . imports a moral <qex>obliquity</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>South.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Oblite</ent>⟦br⟧
